The people of Macedonia decided in a referendum held on Sunday about whether their name would change to "Republic of North Macedonia", a gesture that would resolve a decades-long conflict with Greece, which had blocked their candidate for accession to the European Union and NATO.
Greece, which has a province called Macedonia, maintains that its northern neighbor’s name is a claim of its territory and has vetoed its entry into NATO and the EU.
